Church History

St. Paul's Baptist Church was organized because of need. Many African American families relocated to Conshohocken, Pennsylvania from South Carolina to find employment at the Alan Wood Steel Company. At that time, there was not an African American Baptist Church in Conshohocken where they could worship.

Reverend Marshall W. Lee, a licensed minister, met with these newly relocated African American families. Reverend Lee, who lived in Conshohocken, also desired to worship locally. He was a member of Siloam Baptist Church, Norristown, Pennsylvania. After much encouragement from a local businessman, Walter Woods, he decided to work with these families to establish an African American Baptist Church in Conshohocken.

Several organizational meetings were held in the James Hall Mill located in West Conshohocken. On the first Sunday in April 1925, Reverend Lee invited Mrs. Demmie Milton, Mrs. Mattie Smith, Mr. Walter Woods and Mr. Stephen Soloman to meet with Siloam Baptist Church located in Norristown. The meeting was held to procure letters for the purpose of organizing a Baptist Church in Conshohocken.

On April 29, 1925, the St. Paul's Baptist Church was founded. In March 1926, St. Paul's Baptist Church became incorporated under Pennsylvania Law.

The main structure of the building was erected in 1927 by forty-five (45) dedicated members. The stone for the church was donated by the Alan Wood Steel Company, Conshohocken. In 1950, the first annex where the organ now resides was completed. In 1955, the parsonage was purchased. Stained glass windows were donated by members in 1961. An addition was built in 1967 which joined the church school and parsonage. In 1981, the sanctuary was renovated and a balcony was erected in the rear of the church.

Reverend Marshall W. Lee served as pastor for more than 51 years. Reverend James A. Groves, Sr., served as an assistant to Reverend Lee.

After receiving a call to the ministry, Reverend Groves was ordained and installed as our second pastor in 1977. He served faithfully until his sudden passing in 1997.

On June 22, 1997, Reverend Leon Lowery, an associate pastor of the church, was installed as the third pastor. He served for seven years.

Reverend Mryna E. Graham, an associate pastor of the church, was ordained and installed as the fourth pastor in 2004. She served faithfully until her retirement in May 2010.

Upcoming Events

Grandparents Day will be held on Sunday, September 11 at 10:30 am.  Reverend Bisa Bennett, from Canaan Baptist Church, will be the guest speaker and we will have soloist, Jocelyn Gilliard, from Bethel Deliverance International Church perform, as well.  Dinner will be served immediately following the worship service and gifts will be given to all of the grandparents.  We hope to see you all there!

 

St. Paul's will have a Missionary Day Service on September 25, at 3:30 pm.  The guest speaker will be Evangelist Dorothy White from the Christian Hearts Prayer Church of Coopperas Cove, Texas.  We ask that your congregation, your Missionary Team or representative of your church would join us and celebrate this day with us.  We are looking forward to a great day of worship and fellowship!

~The Missionary Ministry of St. Paul's

Congratulations!

Thought and Reflection


Watch Night Service
New Years Eve 2010

It was a blessed event. Over 50 strong in attendance. We brought in the New Year with communion, song, prayer and praise. Being in the house of the LORD is always good and on this night the message of the evening was "STAY FOCUSED" because "THE BEST IS YET TO COME". We gave thanks for all HE has done and all HE has in store for 2011, you only need to be saved and believe in your heart. At St. Paul's Baptist Church, change is  the order of the day.

What We Believe


THE LORD JESUS CHRIST

We believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God, God manifested in the flesh, true God and true man. We believe in His virgin birth, in His sinless life, in His miracles, in His vicarious and atoning death through His shed blood, in His bodily resurrection, in His ascension to the right hand of the Father, and in His personal return in power and glory.


EXPRESSIONS OF PRAISE

I will bless the Lord at all times; His praise shall continually be in my mouth. 
My soul will make its boast in the Lord; The humble will hear it and rejoice. 
O magnify the Lord with me, And let us exalt His name together.

Psalm 34: 1-3


THE SCRIPTURES


We believe the Bible to be the inspired Word of God, inerrant in the original writings, the complete revelation of God's will for man and the final authority for Christian faith and conduct.


THE ONE TRUE GOD

We believe in one God, the Creator of all things, eternally existing in three persons: Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, who are co-equal and infinitely perfect.
